abstract: The notoriously repressive kingdom will announce a new program as it tries to diversify its economy away from dependence on oil.
snippet: The notoriously repressive kingdom will announce a new program as it tries to diversify its economy away from dependence on oil.
lead_paragraph: So, who wants to go to Saudi Arabia? The government is about to find out.

abstract: Inwood has the lowest average rents in the borough. Now developers and their high-rise buildings are coming.
snippet: Inwood has the lowest average rents in the borough. Now developers and their high-rise buildings are coming.
lead_paragraph: For decades, Inwood has been one of New York City’s untouched gems. Nestled among rivers and rolling forest at the northernmost tip of Manhattan, the 500-acre neighborhood has again and again batted away the forces of gentrification — until now.

abstract: The gift from Stewart and Lynda Resnick, the billionaire owners of bottled water and agriculture companies, comes amid growing urgency over climate change.
snippet: The gift from Stewart and Lynda Resnick, the billionaire owners of bottled water and agriculture companies, comes amid growing urgency over climate change.
lead_paragraph: It will take huge efforts, according to experts, to avert disasters related to climate change. Commitments from reluctant leaders to reform the global economy. Shifts in the daily routines of citizens. And research from the world’s greatest minds — lots of it.

abstract: The lounge brings together former night life rivals Nur Khan and John McDonald.
snippet: The lounge brings together former night life rivals Nur Khan and John McDonald.
lead_paragraph: The F train is late. A Chase branch pops up. A bar opens in a hotel. Most barely merit mention, but the Butterfly, a celebrity-friendly lounge that opened at the Sixty SoHo hotel this spring, is a buzzy exception.
